Hi, 
I am really facing a strange issue. While navigating from one menu to another. The previous page js is getting loaded on a new page and because of that my custom module having form is breaking giving below error.
Uncaught ReferenceError: hbspt is not defined
at <anonymous>:64:9
at x (PreviouspageJavasrcipt.js:7691)
at h (PreviouspageJavasrcipt.js:7685)
at XMLHttpRequest.S.te.onload
If I reload the page, then everything is great. There is no error in the console and page look as per design.
 
When I try to visit the line no. 7685, 7691 from js. Found the above code before the lines giving error.
/*!
* jQuery JavaScript Library v1.11.3
* <http://jquery.com/>
*
* Includes Sizzle.js
* <http://sizzlejs.com/>
*
* Copyright 2005, 2014 jQuery Foundation, Inc. and other contributors
* Released under the MIT license
* <http://jquery.org/license>
*
* Date: 2015-04-28T16:19Z
*/
So it is pretty state forward that the code is from jquery. Where should I modify so that my pages with form look correct when navigated from the previous page.
